Thinking about people growth is essential for nonprofit leaders
>For leaders of nonprofit organizations, it is essential to think about the [growth] of people. People work for nonprofit organizations because they share a [vision] with the organization. It is impossible for a volunteer to work for a long time if he or she has nothing to gain. They have to get a lot out of the work itself because they are not getting paid [financially].

People do [non-profit work] for [growth opportunities] and [learning].
[The OSS Project is also a non-profit organization of sorts.
